						               													<description>A relatively simple 12-turn point-to-point (sudden death) campaign game about General George Patton's attempt to fight through France's Lorraine and break through the fortified Siegfried Line behind the Saar River before Winter 1944.&amp;#10;If his player scores big successes at the start, his fuel may *not* be diverted to Field Marshal Montgomery's (over-, it turned out) ambitious Market Garden paradrop north into Holland.&amp;#10;Abstract regimental/brigade level 27 US pieces, 18 German, and 6 (German) Fogs of War.  (For solitaire play, the German infantrie and FOW pieces can be turned upside down and randomly mixed.)  Optional stand-up pieces for German infantrie and FOW pieces.&amp;#10;50% hit probabilities of Disruption possibly culminatig in elimination.  3 grades of road.  Bonus to US infantry for prepared, artillery supported attacks.&amp;#10;Free to print and play on CoatneyHistory.&amp;#10;Mapboard compatible with classic Champer &amp;amp; Sackson game Major Battles and Campaigns of General George S. Patton (1973), but PLL has a better movement and combat system, including risking No Retreat! orders.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
